This paper is likely to belong to the category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) as it presents a new class of public key algorithms for encryption and signatures. It may also belong to Information Theory (cs.IT) as it discusses the efficiency and speed of the algorithm. Additionally, it could be categorized under Computer Communications (cs.CC) as it mentions the parallelizability of the algorithm. The paper also discusses the implementation of the algorithm on FPGA, which could place it under Computer Engineering (cs.CE). Finally, the use of quasigroups in the algorithm may suggest a connection to Discrete Mathematics and Combinatorics (cs.DS).
